          <div class="slick__slide slide slide--0">      <div class="slide__content">            <a href="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7171.jpeg" class="slick__colorbox litebox" data-media="{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;rel&quot;:&quot;slick-node-14958-photo-gallery-field-image-1&quot;}"><div class="media media--image media--switch"><img typeof="foaf:Image" class="image-style-none" src="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/styles/embedded_gallery_image/public/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7171.jpeg?itok=nTFcvbjr" width="400" height="384" alt="Angled view from the right of a red wall that features a mix of 17 photographs, sketches and paintings on a red wall." title="" /></div><span class="media-icon media-icon--lightbox media-icon--colorbox"></span></a><div class="litebox-caption element-invisible"><figcaption><p>For nearly 250 years, the City of Québec was the political capital and place of residence of the colony’s governors. Following Confederation in 1867, Rideau Hall in Ottawa became the new official residence of the governor general of Canada.</p>

              <ul class="list-unstyled">  
                   
              </ul>
            </figcaption></div>            
      
    </div>  </div>          <div class="slick__slide slide slide--1">      <div class="slide__content">            <a href="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7173.jpeg" class="slick__colorbox litebox" data-media="{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;rel&quot;:&quot;slick-node-14958-photo-gallery-field-image-1&quot;}"><div class="media media--image media--switch"><img typeof="foaf:Image" class="image-style-none" src="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/styles/embedded_gallery_image/public/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7173.jpeg?itok=JbByQzQ-" width="400" height="384" alt="" title="" /></div><span class="media-icon media-icon--lightbox media-icon--colorbox"></span></a><div class="litebox-caption element-invisible"><figcaption><p>For nearly 250 years, the City of Québec was the political capital and place of residence of the colony’s governors. Following Confederation in 1867, Rideau Hall in Ottawa became the new official residence of the governor general of Canada.</p>

              <ul class="list-unstyled">  
                   
              </ul>
            </figcaption></div>            
      
    </div>  </div>          <div class="slick__slide slide slide--2">      <div class="slide__content">            <a href="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7184.jpeg" class="slick__colorbox litebox" data-media="{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;rel&quot;:&quot;slick-node-14958-photo-gallery-field-image-1&quot;}"><div class="media media--image media--switch"><img typeof="foaf:Image" class="image-style-none" src="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/styles/embedded_gallery_image/public/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7184.jpeg?itok=RuDPpRXv" width="400" height="384" alt="There is a large 2-piece display of sketches and text on the left. A red wall featuring a mix of 17 photographs, sketches and paintings is on the right." title="" /></div><span class="media-icon media-icon--lightbox media-icon--colorbox"></span></a><div class="litebox-caption element-invisible"><figcaption><p>In 1872, Lord Dufferin, Governor General from 1872 to 1878, moved into the Citadelle of Québec; in so doing, he re-established the tradition of having a residence for the governor general in the Old Capital, a tradition dating back to the New France era. Since then, every governor general has stayed here in the course of their official duties.</p>

              <ul class="list-unstyled">  
                   
              </ul>
            </figcaption></div>            
      
    </div>  </div>          <div class="slick__slide slide slide--3">      <div class="slide__content">            <a href="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7194.jpeg" class="slick__colorbox litebox" data-media="{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;rel&quot;:&quot;slick-node-14958-photo-gallery-field-image-1&quot;}"><div class="media media--image media--switch"><img typeof="foaf:Image" class="image-style-none" src="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/styles/embedded_gallery_image/public/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7194.jpeg?itok=xvE1s_Nw" width="400" height="384" alt="A painting is hanging above wooden table. There is a chair next to the table. The 150 Years of Viceregal Presence at the Citadelle of Québec exhibit wall is visible in the background." title="" /></div><span class="media-icon media-icon--lightbox media-icon--colorbox"></span></a><div class="litebox-caption element-invisible"><figcaption><p>In 1872, Lord Dufferin, Governor General from 1872 to 1878, moved into the Citadelle of Québec; in so doing, he re-established the tradition of having a residence for the governor general in the Old Capital, a tradition dating back to the New France era. Since then, every governor general has stayed here in the course of their official duties.</p>

              <ul class="list-unstyled">  
                   
              </ul>
            </figcaption></div>            
      
    </div>  </div>          <div class="slick__slide slide slide--4">      <div class="slide__content">            <a href="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7196.jpeg" class="slick__colorbox litebox" data-media="{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;rel&quot;:&quot;slick-node-14958-photo-gallery-field-image-1&quot;}"><div class="media media--image media--switch"><img typeof="foaf:Image" class="image-style-none" src="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/styles/embedded_gallery_image/public/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7196.jpeg?itok=lPOzYnCh" width="400" height="384" alt="View through a wide doorway into a room with a red wall that contains a mix of photographs, sketches and paintings." title="" /></div><span class="media-icon media-icon--lightbox media-icon--colorbox"></span></a><div class="litebox-caption element-invisible"><figcaption><p>This photo exhibition traces the evolution of the buildings that, over the years, have hosted dignitaries from around the world, including many Canadians who have come to receive our country’s highest honours.</p>

              <ul class="list-unstyled">  
                   
              </ul>
            </figcaption></div>            
      
    </div>  </div>          <div class="slick__slide slide slide--5">      <div class="slide__content">            <a href="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7200.jpeg" class="slick__colorbox litebox" data-media="{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image&quot;,&quot;rel&quot;:&quot;slick-node-14958-photo-gallery-field-image-1&quot;}"><div class="media media--image media--switch"><img typeof="foaf:Image" class="image-style-none" src="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/styles/embedded_gallery_image/public/media/galleries/2022/10_14_Citadelle_150/img_7200.jpeg?itok=0bTbP4u0" width="400" height="384" alt="An angled staircase is in the foreground. A table and chairs is in the middle ground. The room containing the 150 Years of Viceregal Presence at the Citadelle of Québec exhibit is in the background." title="" /></div><span class="media-icon media-icon--lightbox media-icon--colorbox"></span></a><div class="litebox-caption element-invisible"><figcaption><p>This photo exhibition traces the evolution of the buildings that, over the years, have hosted dignitaries from around the world, including many Canadians who have come to receive our country’s highest honours.</p>

              <ul class="list-unstyled">  
                   
              </ul>
            </figcaption></div>            
      
